<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="367" pageId="1" pageNumber="366" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1729,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1801,1828]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Description.</emphasis>
Head, pro-, and mesonotum pale ochre yellow with dense brown speckles, mesonotum with brighter yellowish tinge (
<figureCitation box="[435,545,1837,1864]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
). Face somewhat darker in upper part, areas on sides of frons and around ocelli lack speckles. Proepimeron with brownish streak. Forewing semi-transparent with brown speckles more dense on clavus, on costal margin, and in apical half. Veins mostly of the same colour as membrane, transverse veins in apical part brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1729,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">
Apex of crown and anterior margin of pronotum angular (
<figureCitation box="[843,911,1981,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="366">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Median keel very narrow, but distinct on face and pronotum and almost invisible on mesonotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[511,527,152,166]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">nd</superScript>
tergite in male with angular lobes separated by narrow round notch; sternal apodemes narrow, slightly bent inwards, separated by wide more or less rectangular notch (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1272,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Penis in side view almost parallel-sided in apical half, only slightly tapering apically (
<figureCitation box="[961,1045,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Pygofer process in side view narrow, gradually pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[517,601,261,288]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
), in back view strongly diverging, rather wide, with rounded tip (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Style tip shape is typical for the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacobi" authorityYear="1910" box="[513,599,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[513,599,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<figureCitation box="[686,770,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
